com.nerjal.json.elements

Class JsonObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nerjal.json.elements.JsonElement
      • com.nerjal.json.elements.JsonObject

  • public class JsonObject
extends JsonElement

    An object that maps keys to JSON values, allowing to build objects for a JSON structure.

    The object provides a mapping of keys and JsonElement values, including the children JsonComment, and a set of entries, only including non-comment children.

    The objects stringification relies on options set with a ObjectParseOptions attribute, defaulted to match the JSON4 syntax, which can be replaced or instantiated to a different value.
    These options allow to set the keys quoting.

    Author:
    nerjal

      • stringify

        public String stringify(String indentation,
                        String indentIncrement,
                        com.nerjal.json.elements.JsonStringifyStack stack)
                 throws JsonError.RecursiveJsonElementException
        Description copied from class: JsonElement
        Returns the JSON String corresponding to this JsonElement, recursively parsing the internal elements if there are, with the according base indentation and level indent incrementation.
        Parameters:
        indentation - the base indentation at which should be the element, hence the one-lower level of its children
        indentIncrement - the string to increment to the indentation at each indentation level, recursively to the element's children as well as their own, etc.
        stack - The foolproof security check to avoid recursive stringification. Can be null.
        Returns:
        The JSON String corresponding to this element.
        Throws:
        JsonError.RecursiveJsonElementException - If the element or one of its children contains an element already in the stack or one of themselves, which would end up in loop parsing.
